<h3>Shipping Order Import Page</h3>

<p>
  Make sure your file is a CSV format.  So commas need to seperate the columns in the spreadsheet.  You can download an
  example <%= link_to 'here', csv_example_shipping_orders_path %>.</p>
<p>
  There is a unique column in the CSV column for supporting the ability to import mutliple rferences.  The column name is
  "References" (no quotes), in this column you can define multiple references by using this format.</p>
<div class="row alert alert-primary">
  <div class="col">
    PO Number.123.false|DELV05.444.false|Sales Acct.876.false
  </div>
  <div class="col">
    When imported it will show up as:
  </div>
  <div class="col">
    <%= image_tag("references.jpg", :alt => "tms image of references") %>
  </div>

</div>

</p>

<%= form_tag import_shipping_orders_path, multipart: true do %>
<%= file_field_tag :file %>
<%= submit_tag "Import" %>
<% end %>